According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Livestream E-Commerce Market was valued at USD 858.66 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 1.02 trillion in 2025 to USD 2.97 trillion by 2034, registering an impressive CAGR of 19.6% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing exceptional growth as businesses increasingly combine live video streaming with digital commerce to create engaging, interactive, and personalized shopping experiences. Growing smartphone penetration, expanding high-speed internet connectivity, rising social commerce adoption, and increasing consumer preference for real-time product demonstrations are transforming the global retail landscape. Livestream commerce has evolved beyond a marketing trend into a mainstream sales channel, enabling brands to boost customer engagement, improve conversion rates, and strengthen long-term consumer relationships.
